HEADWORD: Theopneusty
<hw>The"op*neus`ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<?/.]</ety> <def>Divine inspiration; the supernatural influence of the
Divine Spirit in qualifying men to receive and communicate revealed
truth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Theorbist</ent>⟦br⟧
